 ('673', '1022', '4', '1', 'en_us', '13', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"EMOTICASH: FINANCE WITH FEELING\",\"slug\":\"emoticash-finance-with-feeling\",\"postDate\":null,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"53\":{\"1023\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>Using the latest Emotional Detection and Recognition (EDR) technology, we provide brands and media companies with your reactions to their products, all through the camera in your phone. In exchange, your responses equate to Emoticash, which you can spend on self-care activities and products such as Gong Baths, Yoga and meditation sessions. Paid to smile. Paid to frown. Paid to be you.<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"1024\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"file\":[\"1026\"],\"size\":\"large\"}},\"1025\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>In the age of mass surveillance, we\\u2019ve realised that consumers have long grown used to being watched. Many view the information exchange between citizen and state that underpins our modern surveillance system as a necessary evil for public safety.<br><br>But one area where, until only a few years ago, the transactional nature of surveillance had not yet been fully explored was in the growing Emotional Detection and Recognition technology market \\u2013 the tracking of human emotions and reactions in industries where such data is vital, for example retail, hospitality and healthcare.<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"1030\":{\"type\":\"pullQuoteImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"\\u201cMining the untapped reserve of human emotion\\u201d\",\"file\":[\"1033\"],\"size\":\"large\"}},\"1035\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>Emoticash (EMOT) aims to answer some of those questions. An evolution of the algorithm employed by popular cryptocurrencies such as Bitcoin (BTC) and Ethereum (ETH), Emoticash seeks to reimburse consumers with spendable currency whenever their emotional information is harvested during an everyday transaction. Your opinion is valuable, and we want to reward you.<\\/p><p>At the core of Emoticash is an aim to restrike the balance of power in the modern surveillance state, placing a price upon the information that many members of the public unwittingly provide to companies countless times a day. If brands and businesses are being empowered by the information they collect from their customers, we believe customers should be empowered in turn, and the provision of spendable currency is the simplest way of achieving this balance.<br><\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"1040\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"file\":[\"1034\"],\"size\":\"large\"}},\"1041\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"file\":[\"1039\"],\"size\":\"large\"}},\"1042\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>In recent years, EDR has proven to be one of the fastest-growing sectors in the tech industry thanks to its broad range of potential applications in retail, education, hospitality, healthcare and more. Realeyes, an EDR tech company with offices in the US and Europe, works with numerous big brands and film production companies to produce \\u201cemotionally intelligent\\u201d visual media. Their proprietary software is able to identify the affective qualities of different media and even help in creating media to target specific demographic groups by metrics such as age or gender.<br><br>Similarly, the Boston-based company Affectiva now boasts a \\u201cmassive emotion database\\u201d, built upon over 6 million scanned faces from over 80 different countries, gathered from users watching films and television shows or performing everyday activities. As well as facial emotion tracking software, Affectiva is currently beta-testing software that will be able to track emotions in speech recordings, as well as the gender of the person speaking.<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"1045\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"file\":[\"1043\"],\"size\":\"large\"}},\"1046\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>In the market, numerous companies, big and small, have already begun experimenting with EDR technology in exciting ways. In 2017, fast food giant Kentucky Fried Chicken experimented with EDR technology at one of their Chinese locations, allowing customers to pay for their meal by smiling, whilst the Chinese police have been using eyeglasses with integrated facial recognition technology for several years. During the 2016 US presidential elections, Hillary Clinton\\u2019s campaign team even used EDR technology to track responses to the Democratic candidate\\u2019s speeches on the campaign trail.<br><br>Though EDR technology remains in its infancy, the development is already providing promising results. The technology that Realeyes uses to gauge an advertisement\\u2019s \\u201cemotional intelligence\\u201d is already able to identify commercials which will produce a sales lift with an accuracy of 75%, while Affectiva\\u2019s Software Development Kit (SDK) has been implemented in a number of children\\u2019s learning apps, as well as being used by popular gif-hosting website Giphy to attach emotional qualities to different images.<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"1047\":{\"type\":\"pullQuoteImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"\\u201cEmoticash partners indicate a 17% increase in consumer engagement with brands through EDR feedback interfaces as opposed to traditional feedback forms and questionnaires.\\u201d\",\"file\":[\"1044\"],\"size\":\"large\"}}},\"52\":\"Welcome to Emoticash, where we bring your feelings into the equation. We believe that consumers should be rewarded for sharing their emotional data, ___________. It takes 26 muscles to smile, or 62 to frown. We accept either as payment.\",\"37\":[\"1020\"]}}', '2018-03-23 00:06:54', '2018-03-23 00:0