loses oneself when one is out of touch with oneself, the first two proposed scenarios would help the weakening of the individual, as in the smart advertising scenario, this technology seeks to understand, target and exploit the reactionary nature of human beings.<br><br>The second scenario, provides that the individual envelops him\\/herself in a mask of normality and cannoned behaviour, diluting their personality.<br><br>The third use, if used within non exploitative parameters, will help the individual know and understand themselves better, and will become a tool for healing and self discovery rather than an extra layer with which curate oneself, or a new channel with which to cloud people\'s existence.<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"1112\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p><strong>DOING THINGS DIFFERENTLY&nbsp;<br><br><\\/strong><em>Services Unknown is an open-ended Superimpose Studio project that facilitates new ideas, discussion, events and product.<br><br><\\/em>Read The Emoticash Report&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/superimpose.studio\\/post\\/emoticash-finance-with-feeling\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">here<\\/a>.<br>Submission of new ideas to&nbsp;<a href=\\\"mailto:hello@superimpose.studio\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">hello@superimpose.studio<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}}},\"52\":\"The second response to our Emoticash project comes from Meri Carrasco, designer and RCA postgrad student who imagines the potential different scenarios that could arise.\",\"37\":[\"1113\"]}}', '2018-04-20 14:25:54', '2018-04-20 14:25:54', '9924f624-a6e2-494c-a994-0ae790f27b15'),
