 the reactionary nature of human beings.<br><br>The second scenario, provides that the individual envelops him\\/herself in a mask of normality and cannoned behaviour, diluting their personality.<br><br>The third use, if used within non exploitative parameters, will help the individual know and understand themselves better, and will become a tool for healing and self discovery rather than an extra layer with which curate oneself, or a new channel with which to cloud people\'s existence.<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"1112\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p><strong>DOING THINGS DIFFERENTLY&nbsp;<br><br><\\/strong><em>Services Unknown is an open-ended Superimpose Studio project that facilitates new ideas, discussion, events and product.<br><br><\\/em>Read The Emoticash Report&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/superimpose.studio\\/post\\/emoticash-finance-with-feeling\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">here<\\/a>.<br>Submission of new ideas to&nbsp;<a href=\\\"mailto:hello@superimpose.studio\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">hello@superimpose.studio<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}}},\"52\":\"The second response to our Emoticash project comes from Meri Carrasco, designer and RCA postgrad student who imagines the potential different scenarios that could arise.\",\"37\":[\"1113\"]}}', '2018-04-23 12:37:21', '2018-04-23 12:37:21', '88b0569c-b98f-4863-9701-0fc9cb3f27f1'),
