e second response to our Post-Ascending Authority statement from Services Unknown comes from Silk Agency founder and freelance writer Lillian He.\",\"37\":[\"1128\"]}}', '2018-04-30 09:58:42', '2018-04-30 09:58:42', '27b19aaf-3d7c-4fa0-ba81-a45b842a8f5b'),
 ('784', '1052', '4', '1', 'en_us', '6', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Post-Ascending Authority: Response #1\",\"slug\":\"paa-response1\",\"postDate\":1521981240,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"53\":{\"1053\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>People now seek realness more than ever - politics, consumerism and the dubious media has all led to truth being dragged through the dirt. The general population is constantly lied to, from half truths to full blown deception. The faces at the top of the once powerful pyramid are no longer a trusted source of information, with a hidden agenda peddled behind every policy, trend and product.<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"1054\":{\"type\":\"pullQuoteImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"Your average consumer trusts their peers more than their teachers, their friends over their family, and their contemporaries over their mentors\",\"file\":[\"1061\"],\"size\":\"medium\"}},\"1055\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>Even the youngest generation of consumer\\u2019s bullshit detector is fined tuned to a level never expected by corporations - and this is causing the mass shift to post-ascending authority. Your average consumer trusts their peers more than their teachers, their friends over their family, and their contemporaries over their mentors. Every hour, every day a news story slides down from the top of our phones - corruption, suspicion, and deceit plague the headlines.<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"1056\":{\"type\":\"pullQuoteImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"it makes rationality to reject the old (tradition) and embrace the new (innovation)\",\"file\":[\"1062\"],\"size\":\"large\"}},\"1057\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>With all this engrained in the 21st century zeitgeist, it makes rationality to reject the old (tradition) and embrace the new (innovation). Learning is moving to a democratized activity. 50% of young people prefer independent methods such as YouTube videos over institutional learning - a clear indicator of the lack of faith in the \\u2018altruistic\\u2019 educational set up and information systems.<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"1058\":{\"type\":\"pullQuoteImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"\\u201cThe customer is always right\\u201d has never rang more true, only now it\\u2019s evolved from satisfaction to dictation.\",\"file\":[\"1064\"],\"size\":\"medium\"}},\"1059\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>It\\u2019s a short leap for this to apply to the everyday objects that surround us - from the beauty products we use to the shoes we wear. Brands are only just beginning to adapt to this new authority and the rapid haste it brings to trends and feedback. \\u201cThe customer is always right\\u201d has never rang more true, only now it\\u2019s evolved from satisfaction to dictation. For the first time post the industrial revolution, individuals and small business can innovate quicker than the industry leaders. These are the ones defining the next jacket trend, music genre, or en vogue fragrance. Power to the people, power to every single person in pursuit of their truth.<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"1069\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"file\":[\"1065\"],\"size\":\"large\"}},\"1070\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>DOING THINGS DIFFERENTLY&nbsp;<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Services Unknown is an open-ended Superimpose Studio project that facilitates new ideas, discussion, events and product.<\\/em><\\/p><p>Read Post-Ascending Authority&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/superimpose.studio\\/post\\/post-asscending-authority\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">here<\\/a>.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nSubmission of new ideas and responses can be received at&nbsp;<a href=\\\"mailto:hello@superimpose.studio\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">hello@superimpose.studio<\\/a><\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}}},\"52\":\"The first response to our \'Post-Ascending Authority\' statement from Services Unknown comes from NYC based Music & Culture consultant Harry Benson.\",\"37\":[\"1068\"]}}', '2018-04-30 14:42:52', '2018-04-30 14:42:52', 'c1487092-57ac-4f1c-b646-d1e22aec4998'),
 ('785', '973', '4', '1', 'en_us', '11', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Post-Ascending Authority\",\"slug\":\"post-asscending-authority\",\"postDate\":1520368260,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"53\":{\"974\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>In modern society, multiple dominant hierarchies may exist at the same time across multiple spheres, each with their own social ranking systems and criteria. An overt example would be China\\u2019s recently devised Social Credit System, in which every citizen is assigned a numerical value designating their social \\u201cworth\\u201d, but the same principle can also be identified in more precarious social hierarchies, such as race, class, education and occupation.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br>But what happens when we witness the failure of these systems \\u2013 or when a system can no longer sufficiently achieve its objective of distribution? Does this serve us better as individuals?&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"990\":{\"type\":\"pullQuoteImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"Are we trading the safety of an institution for the pursuit, and acquisition of personal freedom and power?\",\"file\":[\"997\"],\"size\":\"medium\"}},\"976\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>With this in mind, it\\u2019s possible that we have finally begun to see the promise of Ascending Authority come to fruition.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br><em>Ascending Authority:<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><br>For previous generations, audiences looked to established entities and brands for inspiration and guidance. Attitude was the most vital quality required in order to stand out. <\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><br>Today, this has changed. New thinking can now be found around every street corner, influencing our understanding of the past, the present, the low and the high.<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><br>The next wave of innovators are the keyholders. They choose their inspiration the same way they choose their collaborators. They learn, they broadcast, they fail and they stay up. It changes day to day, hour to hour. Their very mode of being is responsive and never stagnant. <\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><br>When individuals fight for their truth, power and influence can no longer travel in one direction, descending from the top to the bottom. The individual acquires the access, influence and power to armour themselves.<\\/em><\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"977\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"file\":[\"938\"],\"size\":\"large\"}},\"978\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>Where technology\\u2019s proliferation increasingly gave millennials a voice with which they could interact with brands, Gen Z are now moving one step further. They don\\u2019t respond to brands; brands respond to them. This new power shift has already initiated a flurry of smaller changes, such as the increased co-creation and customisation of products, crowdsourced campaigns and the rise of micro-influencers that shun the spotlight over big celebrities that openly court fame. <\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"979\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"file\":[\"940\"],\"size\":\"large\"}},\"980\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>Subtle drivers are impacting brand manoeuvres worldwide as they come to terms with the notion of being reactive, existing in a climate of \'opt in\\u2019 or \\u2018opt out\'. Nobody is falling in line and simply doing as told. Where once a systemic framework drove the formation, cohesion and continued existence of an ecosystem, that same framework is now being broken, and new bridges being built, in a way that will radically alter the way our consumptive society functions, if not transforming it altogether. Indeed, many old institutions have already been caught out and forced to change the foundations of their ideas and communications. Others, too slow to react and too complacent in the status quo, have collapsed entirely.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br>Major changes are happening inside the old hierarchies that once arranged and organised our society. The \\u201cascending authority\\u201d \\u2013 younger generations leading trends and movements from the bottom up \\u2013 are now becoming astute listeners, confident decision makers and pragmatic movers. From magazine publications and fashion houses to tech circles and even political parties, the old guard is waking up to an uncomfortable proposition; prepare for replacement, by choice or by force. The new wave has opened the door and is in the boardroom, and they\\u2019re not there to gain a better view. They\\u2019re there to hold their own conversation, and to keep the door open for the next group.<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"981\":{\"type\":\"pullQuoteImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"The new wave has opened the door and is in the boardroom, and they\\u2019re not there to gain a better view.\",\"file\":[\"939\"],\"size\":\"medium\"}},\"982\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>In 2018, we may have reached the year that marks the beginning of the next phase; the \\u2018post-ascending authority\\u2019. Young people and marginalised groups\\u2019 cultural takeover is no longer the next phase; it is the norm. This year began with unease and turbulence, but it is within this instability that we acclimatise and evolve. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>So, the big question is this: Now that the youth have found themselves finally in a position to shape the future, what does that future look like?<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"984\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>Stay tuned for a series of responses to come from industry thought leaders.<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"983\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>DOING THINGS DIFFERENTLY&nbsp;<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Services Unknown is an open-ended Superimpose Studio project that facilitates new ideas, discussion, events and product.<\\/em><\\/p><p>Read response #1 from Harry Benson&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/superimpose.studio\\/post\\/paa-response1\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">here.<\\/a><\\/p><p>Read response #2&nbsp;from Lillian He&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/superimpose.studio\\/post\\/paa-response-2\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">here.<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nSubmission of new ideas and responses can be received at&nbsp;<a href=\\\"mailto:hello@superimpose.studio\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">hello@superimpose.studio<\\/a><\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\",\"position\":\"left\"}}},\"52\":\"Dominance hierarchy is a phenomenon in which a clear hierarchy is established within a social group, often through aggression or force. Once a dominance hierarchy is established, the dominant group will often create a social ranking system to designate how, where and when members of different social groups may interact. These ranking systems apportion different levels of value to people in different groups, who will then have to compete for access to resources, services and opportunities. \\r\\n\",\"37\":[\"941\"]}}', '2018-04-30 14:43:36', '2018-04-30 14:43:36', '22713da0-afa9-4a6a-b6b2-bff4e26be3b9'),
 ('786', '1145', '4', '1', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Post-Ascending Authority: Response #3\",\"slug\":\"paa_3\",\"postDate\":null,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"53\":\"\",\"52\":\"\",\"37\":\"\"}}', '2018-05-16 15:52:54', '2018-05-16 15:52:54', 'f4945fda-3d62-46db-aa36-e9cc8a50692a'),
 ('787', '1145', '4', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Post-Ascending Authority: Response #3\",\"slug\":\"paa_3\",\"postDate\":null,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"53\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>When UK broadcasters were able to convert the prospect of product placement in TV into reality, it was a game changer. Then, as documentary programming moved online, even more questions started to tag around the content bubble. How could the purity in message survive to affront its editorial integrity? Could this integrity be maintained in the wild west of online content?<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"file\":[\"1149\"],\"size\":\"large\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>There was a feeling in-between cautiousness and fear for digital content creation. Can audiences discern between fact and fiction? Would lines become too blurred and brands exert an even more powerful influence over the content they were supporting?<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The unease within content publishing landscape brewed for some time until the regulatory frameworks caught up.<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>In hindsight, I think we gave too little credit to the next generation of consumers and their in built filter between digital and reality. They are the most astute when it comes to identifying this particular kind of influence and manipulation. With their index fingers swiping screens and able to navigate between the real and constructed, their sense of \\u2018genuinity\\u2019 and developed coping mechanisms are becoming far more superior.<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"new5\":{\"type\":\"pullQuoteImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"Now that this era of post-ascending authority is arriving, what does this generation have to offer, what might they do differently?\",\"file\":[\"1151\"],\"size\":\"small\"}},\"new6\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>There is a baton carried on from millennials in regards to responsibility and impact. They are forcing companies to think harder about what they stand for beyond product and taglines - this new generation is skilled at spotting tokenism and bandwagon jumping. With this, it\\u2019s a race in which the tortoise wins every time. Advertising messages are cleverly finessed but fake, content providers, publishers and brands are being held to account in terms of working practices, political alliances and belief systems as well as the actual product they are putting forward. <\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"new7\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"file\":[\"1148\"],\"size\":\"medium\"}},\"new8\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>In the search for originality, the desirable comes from unexpected avenues, from the lives of the ordinary but unique. We\\u2019re celebrating the normal, looking to things which are meaningful because they are actually attainable - that\\u2019s what is attractive. The question is, how easy is this is to replicate and discern from if it comes from the other direction? Can ideas and influence flow in both directions?<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"new9\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"file\":[\"1150\"],\"size\":\"medium\"}},\"new10\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>If we can strive to a respectful interchange that fuels a different type of creativity for the future, one in which brands, publishers, consumers, leaders and decision makers enjoy unfettered access to the needs and desires of each other, perhaps this is the kind of world we would all like to live in. A world where criticism, distaste, praise and discussion can all happen under the same roof unhindered by the constructs of whichever \\u2018channel\\u2019 we are present across.<\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}},\"new12\":{\"type\":\"image\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"file\":[\"1146\"],\"size\":\"small\"}},\"new11\":{\"type\":\"copy\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>DOING THINGS DIFFERENTLY&nbsp;<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em>Services Unknown is an open-ended Superimpose Studio project that facilitates new ideas, discussion, events and product.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br>Read Post-Ascending Authority&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/superimpose.studio\\/post\\/post-asscending-authority\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">here<\\/a>.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n<br>You can read&nbsp;response #1 from Harry Benson&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/superimpose.studio\\/post\\/paa-response1\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">here<\\/a>&nbsp;and response #2 from Lililan He&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/superimpose.studio\\/post\\/PAA_2\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">here<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n<br>Submission of new ideas and responses can be received at&nbsp;<a href=\\\"mailto:hello@superimpose.studio\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">hello@superimpose.studio<\\/a><\\/p>\",\"position\":\"full\"}}},\"52\":\"The second response to our Post-Ascending Authority statement from Services Unknown comes from AgCa founder and Commissioning Editor for Nowness & Conde Nast Avi Grewal.\",\"37\":[\"1152\"]}}', '2018-05-16 16:05:04', '2018-05-16 16:05:04', 'cb753321-06e0-43b5-95f4-1b33c857a081'),
